SIMPLE: sectarian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sectarian
<hw>Sec*ta"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to a
sect, or to sects; peculiar to a sect; bigotedly attached to the tenets
and interests of a denomination; <as>as, <ex>sectarian</ex> principles
or prejudices</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sectarian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sectarian
<hw>Sec*ta"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a sect; a member or
adherent of a special school, denomination, or religious or
philosophical party; one of a party in religion which has separated
itself from established church, or which holds tenets different from
those of the prevailing denomination in a state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Heretic</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sectarianism</ent>⟦br⟧
